1) sbin :
-> here sbin is called system libraries
-> basically system binaries is commands or binary files used to manage the system.

2) lib :
-> here lib is called the libraries 
-> as a user we dont use this libraries these libraries is used by the Linux kernel

3) boot :
-> here these commands is used to start or restart the Linux machine we can see in ec2 instance.

4) bin :
-> there is slight difference between the sbin and bin that is bin stands for user binaries.
-> these are not admin actions any one can access these commands. so inside bin commands is non administrative.

5) srv :
-> here srv is nothing but server 
-> here in this we can store the configuration files or any imp info related to web server.

6) opt :
-> opt is a very imp folder in Linux.
-> for example if you want to install the third party tools in Linux machine we will use the folder 

7) mnt :
